//Recurring Talks. Play every 4 days - 1st line starts everything
@0 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Yes, <CHARNAME>? Is there something you wish to say?~
@1 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~No, Mazzy. Let's continue.~

@2 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I just wanted to tell you how beautiful you are.~
@3 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Why thank you <CHARNAME>. That lightens my <DAYNIGHTALL>.~

@4 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~May I kiss you?~
@5 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Out in the open? Very well, one kiss in public. More kisses in private.~

@6 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I just wanted to give you this flower.~
@7 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>, I will attach it to my armour. One can never have too many flowers about one's person.~

@8 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~In my experience, Mazzy, most halflings don't venture out into the world. Shouldn't you be at home, growing crops and raising children?~
@9 /*Mazzy*/ =~That was the life laid out before me. I had only to accept it and it would be mine. But I could not live like that, seeing the same people and doing the same things every day, growing old within a few miles of the place where I was born.~
@10 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I wanted to see the world, <CHARNAME>! I wanted to test myself against those who sought to do others harm. You're going to think me foolish, but I dreamed of becoming a paladin.~
@11 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I didn't think there were any halfling paladins.~
@12 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~*snort* As if. You are only a halfling, Mazzy, and you should not try to be what you cannot.~
@13 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Why would you want to be one of those sticks in the mud?~
@14 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Good for you, Mazzy. Everyone should dream that big.~
@15 /*Mazzy*/ = ~As far as I know, there are not. I will be the first.~
@16 /*Mazzy*/ = ~You are not the first to doubt me but I will persist nonetheless. Clearly, though, I should not expect much aid from you.~
@17 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Some paladins tend to be overly rule-bound, it is true, but they are still a force for good: protecting the innocent and making the world a better place. It is my calling.~
@18 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I have not been entirely successful so far, but I do not regret my choice.~
@19 /*Mazzy*/ = ~We can talk about this at greater length another time. For now let us continue.~

@20 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~You seem very fond of Pala. Are you and your sister close?~
@21 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Yes, we are, though she does not share my need for wandering. Pala dreams of a husband and a family, not of swords and battle, but she has always respected my desires just as I acknowledge hers.~
@22 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Still, she is a powerful fighter and has participated in many skirmishes to protect our home. She is much like our father. He was a great fighter but he always said that true warriors stayed home to protect their loved ones.~
@23 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I have not followed his wishes.~
@24 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I am sure that he would still be proud of you.~
@25 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~He sounds amazing, as does Pala. I hope I can get to know her better.~
@26 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I wonder what he would think of me.~
@27 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I hope so, though I doubt it.~
@28 /*Mazzy*/ = ~However, I do not wish to speak about this now. Let us go on travelling.~
@29 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I would like that, <CHARNAME>.~
@30 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Oh, terrible things, most likely. My father never liked anyone who dared to court his daughters. But he taught us to think for ourselves as well and I believe he would have respected my choice.~

@31 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~You grew up here in Trademeet? What was it like?~
@32 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I imagine my childhood was much like any other. I played with my friends and spent time with my sister. My father was part of the local militia so he taught me how to fight. We often visited family in the countryside. It was a normal, happy existence.~
@33 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~That does sound nice.~
@34 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I wish my own childhood had been so idyllic.~
@35 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~A normal, happy existence. I wonder what that would have been like.~
@36 /*Mazzy*/ = ~You did not like Candlekeep? You have spoken of it fondly in the past.~
@37 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~*shrug* It was the only home I ever knew.~
@38 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I was not unhappy. But sometimes I was quite bored.~
@39 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~The scholars were more fond of books than children. I think that's why I became so close to Imoen.~
@40 /*Mazzy*/ = ~The world is so small when we are children. It's amazing how large it actually is, how little we have seen. I could live one thousand years and not see all of it.~
@41 /*Mazzy*/ = ~There are worse things in life than boredom, <CHARNAME>.~
@42 /*Mazzy*/ = ~And with that you gained a life-long friend. One that you are willing to venture to the ends of the earth to save. That seems like a worthwhile childhood to me.~
@43 /*Mazzy*/ = ~But come, let us move on.~

@44 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I saw your mother, Vara, cast several minor spells. Is she some sort of mage?~
@45 /*Mazzy*/ = ~She is a conjurer and the only halfling spellcaster I know. It is because of her that I always believed I could become a paladin.~
@46 /*Mazzy*/ = ~If you ask her, she will say that she is only a minor mage, but that was still a major feat for the daughter of a farmer. She prefers ordinary, useful magic: spells to till the soil, cook a meal, or repair a hole in the roof. Magic that is used to harm others only poisons the caster, that's what she always says.~
@47 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~You mother sounds quite sensible. I think we'll get along.~
@48 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~From what I have seen, your mother may be right.~
@49 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~That's why I do all my fighting with weapons instead. Just a good clean stabbing all around.~
@50 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~But... that's my favorite kind of magic. We'd likely all be dead without offensive spells.~
@51 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I hope so, <CHARNAME>.~
@52 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I believe so too, <CHARNAME>, though I am also willing to inflict death when necessary.~
@53 /*Mazzy*/ = ~*laughs* Some days I quite agree. But you probably shouldn't say that where she can hear.~
@54 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Some days I quite agree. But you probably shouldn't say that where she can hear.~

@55 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Do you have any other siblings?~
@56 /*Mazzy*/ = ~No, it's just me and my sister. A small family for halflings, I know, but my mother says that two was plenty. We've certainly given her plenty of trouble through the years.~

@57 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Can you tell me about Danno?~
@58 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Danno is a strong fighter, a good soul, and while he is a bit foolish, he loves my sister very much. They met while training together as children in the guardhouse and have been inseparable ever since.~
@59 /*Mazzy*/ = ~My father always loved Danno and trained him like the son he never had.~

@60 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~May I ask what happened to your father?~
@61 /*Mazzy*/ = ~You want to know about my father?~
@62 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Well... I...~
@63 /*Mazzy*/ = ~No, <CHARNAME>, not today. Another time.~

@64 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I've always wanted to have sex in a place like this.~
@65 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Lie together? Here?~
@66 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Well, I do like the outdoors. The sun, the sky, the breeze. We will just have to find a place away from prying eyes and ears.~

@67 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I want you, right here, right now.~
@68 /*Mazzy*/ = ~And I want you as well, <CHARNAME>, but you are in no condition for us to lie together. We should rest when we can and afterwards there will be time for us to play.~

@69 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Can you tell me about Patrick?~
@70 /*Mazzy*/ = ~He was my love, though I knew him only a short while. He was good and kind and beautiful and now he has fallen.~
@71 /*Mazzy*/ = ~But he will always be in my heart. That is all I will say right now.~

@72 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Are you willing to say more about Patrick?~
@73 /*Mazzy*/ = ~He is no more, <CHARNAME>. That is all that needs to be said.~
@74 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I loved him and I lost him but I shall always carry the memory of his courage and honour with me.~
@75 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Thank you, Mazzy. That is all I will ask.~
@76 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I would know about his life if it is not too painful. How did you meet, what was he like?~
@77 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~But why did you love him in the first place?~
@78 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~He was the love of your life but I know nothing about him. Will you tell me anything?~
@79 /*Mazzy*/ = ~We met in Trademeet. Patrick was a dashing fighter, clad head to toe in magical Darkmail and wielding Duskblade, a legendary Halbard longer than he was tall. Powerful, handsome, valiant, kind-hearted, loyal to his friends and merciful to his enemies.~
@80 /*Mazzy*/ = ~He always believed that our differences should be solved with words instead of violence whenever possible. That was how we fell so easily into the Shade Lord's trap. Some creatures should not be negotiated with.~
@81 /*Mazzy*/ = ~When he died, he took a part of my heart with him.~
@82 /*Mazzy*/ = ~That will have to be enough for today. Let us move on.~

@83 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Just that I love everything about you. Your pleasant smile, your beautiful form, your deadly arrows...~
@84 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Thank you, <CHARNAME>, I will accept your flattery.~

@85 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Actually, there was something... Back in Candlekeep, there was this book with the most amazing pictures. The book was a manual about couples... uh... coupling and there were some things that seemed quite interesting.~
@86 /*Mazzy*/ = ~And now you'd like to try them out?~
@87 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~If you don't mind.~
@88 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Well, I wouldn't want you to get bored.~
@89 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I might not be that flexible, but I think it's worth a shot.~
@90 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I am always up for new things. Next time we are together you must tell me all about it.~

@91 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Yes, I was thinking about our future.~
@92 /*Mazzy*/ = ~What about us?~
@93 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Mazzy, what do you want from me? From us?~
@94 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~Are you serious about us? Or is this just a bit of fun?~
@95 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~I was just thinking about how much I love you and that I would never give you up.~
@96 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I want what we have now. This is the life I have always dreamed of. We are seeing the world, protecting those in need, and killing those who live to cause pain to innocents.~
@97 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I love the rush of battle, of pushing my body and my skills to their limits. I love seeing the joy of the people we aid when their prayers are finally answered. And I love falling asleep every night, exhausted and satisfied in your arms.~
@98 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I am having fun, <CHARNAME>, but I am also serious. This is the life I have always wanted. We are seeing the world, protecting those in need, and ridding these lands of those who live to cause pain to others.~
@99 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I love you too, <CHARNAME>, but I will not pretend that I can keep you forever. Change, after all, is the only constant in our lives. I know you are here today and that is enough for me.~
@100 /*Mazzy*/ = ~I am happy. This is the life I have always wanted, <CHARNAME>. We are seeing the world, protecting those in need, and ridding these lands of those who live to cause pain to others.~
@101 /*Mazzy*/ = ~Does that answer your concerns?~
@102 /*CHARNAME*/ = ~And the future?~
